# Alabama Trail System Web GIS Map

# Overview
This project is a web-based GIS application that visualizes existing and proposed trail systems across Alabama. It provides an interactive map where users can explore current trails and planned future routes, along with their spatial relationships.
The purpose of this project is to support planning and communication around trail development using a simple web mapping interface.

# Built With
- ArcGIS Pro (data preparation and processing)  
- HTML, CSS, JavaScript  
- Leaflet (web mapping library)  
- ArcGIS Online services  
- Hosted using GitHub Pages  

# Features
- Interactive map of Alabama trail systems  
- Separate layers for existing and proposed trails  
- Zoom and pan navigation  
- Clickable features with basic attribute information  
- Lightweight web-based interface (runs directly in the browser)  

# Live Demo
The project can be viewed here:  
https://samg1199.github.io/Alabama-Trail-Map/

# Purpose
This project was built to support Alabama Sweet Trails by providing a working online map and web application for visualizing trail data. It also demonstrates skills in:
- Web GIS development  
- Mapping and visualizing transportation and trail networks  
- Working with spatial data in a web environment  
- Deploying projects using GitHub Pages  
